    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "We start a band (or a blog) to share our art with the world. To change things. To enjoy ourselves. Or to ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "hone",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " our craft.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "link-0",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://seths.blog/2019/06/writing-not-plastics-not-wall-street/"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And then we quit. Because we had a falling out. Because our fingers are sore. Because of something someone said. Or because we're out of good ideas.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Which is to say, we so often quit for all the wrong reasons.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Of course, the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "only",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "good reason you should quit something you're good at is because you've forgotten how to enjoy it, and you don't miss remembering, either.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
